{
  "text": "where \u03b8 1 is the publicly known type of country 1 (i.e. country 1 cannot lie about its type) and\u03b8 2 is the reported type of country 2. The first-best agreement y F B will [CITATION_1] Optimal contracting under type-dependent reservation utilities has been extensively analyzed in the literature in the case of a single agent [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and in the case of multiple agents [CITATION_5] . Here, due to the convexity of the outside option and the fact that the distribution of types is uniform, we are in a simple case in which the critical type is at the bottom of the distribution.",
